.TH "get_tty_driver" 9 "get_tty_driver" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
get_tty_driver \- find device of a tty
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct tty_driver *" get_tty_driver
.BI "(dev_t device "  ","
.BI "int *index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
device identifier
.IP "index" 12
returns the index of the tty

This routine returns a tty driver structure, given a device number
and also passes back the index number.

Locking: caller must hold tty_mutex
